==English==
=== Etymology ===
Comes from Middle English ''melancolie'', from Late Latin ''melancholia'', from Greek ''melankholi'', from ''melan''-, meaning "black", and ''khol'', meaning "bile."

=== Noun ===
'''melancholy'''
#Great sadness or depression; gloom.

